A Streamlit-based interactive web application that uses **MET Museum Open API**, **OpenAI GPT models**, and **art-historical curatorial prompting** to generate museum-quality interpretations of artworks related to **Ancient Greek mythology**.

This project is developed as part of the course **Arts & Advanced Big Data**, which included five major AI-creative project directions:

### ğŸ“š Final Project Directions from the Course
- **AI Museum Curator** (this project)  
- **Generative AI for Art Creation**  
- **Multimodal Prompting**  
- **Art Data Visualization**  
- **Creative Coding: Generative Poster 2.0**  

This project specifically expands **AI Museum Curator**, combining real museum data with AI-driven curatorial writing and interactive visualization.

